                <p>Urology is a specialized branch of medicine that focuses on the diagnosis and treatment of disorders related to the urinary tract and male reproductive system. This field encompasses a wide range of conditions, including urinary incontinence, kidney stones, bladder infections, and prostate issues. Urologists are highly trained to perform both medical and surgical interventions, utilizing advanced technologies such as minimally invasive techniques and robotic surgery to enhance patient recovery and outcomes.</p>
