            <h2>Some of the most found Urologic Diseases:</h2>
            <p>Below-mentioned are some of the common urologic disorders:</p>
            <h6><strong>Benign Prostatic Hyperplasia:</strong></h6>
            <p>Benign Prostatic Hyperplasia is defined as the expansion in the size of the prostate gland, which is mostly found in older men. BPH can directly invite cancer, and its symptoms can be noticed by the pressure that an increased prostate can place on the urethra. The urethra is defined as the narrow tube that takes urine from the bladder and then relieves it out of the body.</p>
            <h6><strong>Urinary Incontinence:</strong></h6>
            <p>Urinary Incontinence is caused when the bladder becomes uncontrollable, which results in the inconvenient leakage of urine. Some of the most common causes include:</p>
            <ol type="i">
                <li>Diabetes</li>
                <li>Urinary tract infections</li>
                <li>Spinal Cord injury</li>
                <li>Severe Constipation</li>
                <li>Parkinson’s and Multiple Sclerosis kind of diseases</li>
                <li>Weak bladder Muscles</li>
                <li>Pregnancy or Childbirth</li>
            </ol>
            <h6><strong>Urinary Tract Infections:</strong></h6>
            <p>UTI is caused by pathogenic bacteria or viruses that enter the urinary tract and give birth to unwanted infection. These are most commonly found in women, and least in men. Some of the common symptoms are burning sensation during urination, frequent need to urinate, and feeling more to urinate even after urinating.</p>
            <h6><strong>Kidney and Ureteral Stones:</strong></h6>
            <p>Kidney Stone is one of the most common problems noticed nowadays. Stones are found in the kidney when there are crystals in the urine or small particles collect or surround these crystals. These stones can cause extensive pain and can also block the way of urine flow. Small stones can be easily discharged from the patient’s body, but larger ones need to be solved on time otherwise they can be problematic.</p>
        </div>
